# Life Simulation Engine

> **Every choice matters. Shape your character's future one decision at a time.**

## Overview

Life Simulation Engine is a C++ console-based simulation game developed using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles. The project allows users to control a virtual character and make daily life decisions that influence long-term outcomes.

Players navigate through multiple simulated days by choosing activities such as studying, working, exercising, and resting. Each decision affects important life attributes including health, energy, money, skills, and happiness. The simulation demonstrates how consistent daily habits and choices can shape a person's future.

## Features

* Interactive text-based gameplay
* Multiple daily decision options
* Dynamic character progression system
* Health, Energy, Money, Skill, and Happiness management
* Random life events and opportunities
* Performance evaluation and final life report
* Realistic cause-and-effect decision making
* User-friendly console interface

## Technologies Used

* C++
