## OOP Concepts Implemented

### Encapsulation

Character attributes and behaviors are managed through classes and controlled access mechanisms.

### Inheritance

Specialized classes can inherit common functionality from base classes.

### Polymorphism

Functions can behave differently depending on the objects that invoke them.

### Modularity

The project is divided into independent modules for better organization and maintainability.

